npm run dev

http://localhost:3000

build and push (local): 
docker build -t my-website .
docker tag my-website:latest <your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-website:latest
aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | \
  docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/veridical-manufacturing
docker push <your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-website:latest

Run Docker container:
ssh -i ~/.ssh/my-website-key-pair.pem ec2-user@ec2-23-22-150-9.compute-1.amazonaws.com
aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | \
  docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-website
docker-compose pull 
docker-compose down --remove-orphans
docker-compose up -d

stop docker container:
docker stop my-website
docker rm my-website


Forward webhooks to your local server:

1) start port 
 stripe listen --forward-to http://localhost:3000/api/stripe-webhook

2) copy webhook seceret to .env

3) Trigger test events

stripe trigger payment_intent.succeeded
